aspsms-t by Marco Balmer <mb@micressor.ch> @2006
================================================

Check this site for the latest version of this software.

http://www.micressor.ch/content/projects/aspsms-t

Features
--------
* It supports simple text SMS with a maximum of 160 characters. If your message 
  is >160 characters, aspsms-t will split it automatically in more than one part.
* Support for Arabic and other oriental characters up to 87 characters each sms.
* Delivery notification for each sms with a unique transaction number
* It can set alphanumeric originator of every sms. This can be a mobile phone or a 
  short text with a maximum of 11 characters.

Requirements for Debian
-----------------------

* apt-get install libobject-multitype-perl
* apt-get install libauthen-sasl-perl
* apt-get install libdigest-sha1-perl
* apt-get install libxml-parser-perl
* apt-get install libwww-perl
* apt-get install liburi-perl
* apt-get install wget

Requirements for Fedora
-----------------------
yum install perl-Net-Server
yum install perl-Authen-SASL
yum install perl-Digest-SHA1
yum install perl-XML-Parser
yum install (liburi and libwww for perl???)

Overview
--------
aspsms-t is an open source /*GPL*/ (http://www.fsf.org/licensing/licenses/gpl.txt) jabber2sms 
transport, which allows you to send sms messages over the jabber network through the gateway-system 
of aspsms.com (https://www.aspsms.com). A lot of networks are supported.

Normal TextSMS messages usually costs 1 aspsms Credit. aspsms-t deliver very fast and will send 
you a jabber status message. A second message will receive,If your sms was successfully delivered 
to the mobile device.

Configuration with jabbed14
---------------------------

1) Add the following lines to jabber.xml for jabberd14:

<service id='sms-linker'>
 <host>sms.domain.ch</host>
 <accept>
  <ip>127.0.0.1</ip>
  <port>5245</port>
  <secret>secret</secret>
  <timeout>30</timeout>
 </accept>
</service>

Restart your jabberd.

DNS configuration
-----------------

Add the SRV Record to the dns zone:
_xmpp-server._tcp.sms.domain.ch. 900 IN SRV 1 1 5269 domain.ch.

Restart your nameserver.

aspsms-t configuration
----------------------

* Copy ./etc/aspsms.xml.dist to aspsms.xml and configure it

* Configuring the delivery notification agent 
  (not necessary for running aspsms-t --> optional)

  shell> cd /home/www/website
  shell> mkdir aspsms
  shell> cd aspsms
  shell> cp $ASPSMS_PATH/web-notify.pl .
  shell> cp $ASPSMS_PATH/etc/aspsms-web-notify.xml.dist aspsms-web-notify.xml
  shell> chmod 755 web-notify.pl aspsms-web-notify.xml

* Configuring the aspsms-web-notify.xml configuration file.

Running
-------
./aspsms-t.pl -c aspsms.xml

Better you're running aspsms-t under daemontools from djb http://cr.yp.to/daemontools.html
and then check /var/log/messages ;)

